  "description": [
    "ft 31 n Br J Vt mV B c tf Sf jO w 4MS0ED TUESDAYS AHD FRIDAYS W N ARMSTRONC EDITOR TUESDAY JANUARY 4 1898 A I1APPY NEW YEAH The Advertiser wishes a Happy 3Tew Year to the children They have the beautiful illusions of liope We Avish that they may do better than many of us who garnered as Thoreau said in our youth the materials for building palaces and throwing out bridges to the moon but in our middle life are quite content with turning them into plain woodsheds and humble resting places And a Happy 2sew Year to the young people who have the concerns of love and marriage before them If Love be blind marriage And a Happy Xew Year to the old who have traveled long on the highway and now see the glimmer of the lights in the Wayside Inn Where toil shall cease And rest begin And a Happy Xew Year to the poor but the poor are only tliov who feel poor and by desiring little become rich And a Happy 2s ew Year to ihe unfortunate rich It is easier for a camel to go through the eye f a needle"
